snippet.textDisplay: Happy Birthday from one Sag to another! It sometimes takes the experience of being the 30 and beyond years to understand how special being born at this time of the year can be. Getting pass all though years where it feels lost in the  goings on of Christmas to realize we are children conceived from the joy of Spring's arrival. Our parents felt the newness and strength of new life blossoming around them. We, Sagittarians, are the ones that are able to bring that joy, strength and sunshine on the darkest of Winter's days. We cry when joy is in abundance and learn how to laugh at the tragedies. We take it all in, pain, joy, sorrow, silence and become something more, something stronger, something touching a greater depths of our human mystery. Happy Birthday!
